Bay 14th Street, at the N.E. corner of Cropsey Ave; at the left is Cropsey Ave.

January 11, 1931.

P. L. Sperr.

Dyker Beach Park: From Cropsey Ave. at Fourteenth Ave., showing in a set of three views looking northwest and southwest the made land in the Park. In view No. 1 is seen the Polytechnic Preparatory School (towered building). In view No. 2 is seen a promontory, around which will be extended Shore Road.

June 9, 1932.

P. L. Sperr.
